WEBVTT

00:15.187 --> 00:18.846
[gong tolls loudly]

00:18.880 --> 00:22.884
[man prays in foreign language]

00:38.383 --> 00:42.559
[woman sings in
foreign language]

01:19.458 --> 01:24.291
♪ Blue jeans, magazines,
low ridin' rockin' scenes ♪

01:24.325 --> 01:26.603
♪ She's gonna have a good time

01:26.638 --> 01:31.643
♪ Red bull body shots, show
the boys what you got ♪

01:32.092 --> 01:33.610
♪ She's lookin' so fine

01:33.645 --> 01:37.373
♪ She never dreamed she'd
dance in this crazy new world ♪

01:37.407 --> 01:41.342
♪ Breakin' in, workin' out
in a Cinderella swirl ♪

01:41.377 --> 01:44.932
♪ And now she's one
all-American girl ♪

01:46.623 --> 01:48.487
♪ An all-American girl

01:51.594 --> 01:56.737
♪ Big screen movie stars,
loud bars, racing cars ♪

01:56.978 --> 01:59.153
♪ She's crossin' the line

01:59.188 --> 02:03.226
♪ MySpace, pretty face,
red, white and blue lace ♪

02:03.261 --> 02:05.884
♪ Show me yours,
I'll show you mine ♪

02:05.918 --> 02:09.577
♪ She never dreamed she'd
dance in this crazy new world ♪

02:09.612 --> 02:11.303
♪ Breakin' in, workin' out

02:11.338 --> 02:14.168
- Mom, I told you you
shouldn't eat that.

02:14.203 --> 02:15.825
Oh, come on, don't give me that.

02:15.859 --> 02:18.172
You know you have
to start juicing.

02:18.207 --> 02:19.863
I know but you have to do it.

02:19.898 --> 02:20.968
It's really important.

02:21.002 --> 02:22.521
- Bye
-You're late!

02:22.556 --> 02:23.798
- The meeting started?

02:23.833 --> 02:25.697
- Oh, when you're late, you're
usually late for something,

02:25.731 --> 02:26.939
hence, you're late.

02:29.804 --> 02:31.944
- Pretty sassy for an
intern talkin' to a boss.

02:31.979 --> 02:34.947
[elevator dings]

02:34.982 --> 02:36.811
Stop it!

02:36.846 --> 02:38.537
[girls laughing]
[girls mumbling]

02:38.572 --> 02:39.883
- Oh, my God!

02:39.918 --> 02:41.747
Alright, alright.

02:41.782 --> 02:43.128
Let's get on it.

02:43.163 --> 02:44.819
Alexa, have you
finished that story

02:44.854 --> 02:46.373
on winter trends on the city?

02:46.407 --> 02:48.927
- Oh, I'm just waiting on
proofs and then it's a go.

02:48.961 --> 02:49.893
- Okay.

02:49.928 --> 02:51.688
Light a fire under that
photographer's ass,

02:51.723 --> 02:52.689
please? [chuckles]

02:52.724 --> 02:54.277
- Literally, because I
almost got arrested

02:54.312 --> 02:55.175
last time I did that.

02:55.209 --> 02:58.005
[girls laugh loudly]

02:58.039 --> 02:59.455
- And who was boss last night?

03:00.732 --> 03:02.251
When do I get to see you again?

03:03.735 --> 03:05.081
- I got a three
times and out rule

03:05.115 --> 03:06.772
and you used it
all up last night!

03:09.499 --> 03:10.259
- Oh!
- Sorry.

03:10.293 --> 03:11.536
- There she is!

03:11.570 --> 03:14.435
Good morning or is
it good afternoon?

03:14.470 --> 03:15.781
- Sorry.

03:15.816 --> 03:17.507
I was held up in the hallway.

03:17.542 --> 03:20.372
- Held up or bent over?

03:20.407 --> 03:22.754
[Alexa laughs softly]

03:23.548 --> 03:24.652
- Okay.

03:24.687 --> 03:26.447
Claws in, ladies.

03:27.759 --> 03:28.898
I have an announcement.

03:30.382 --> 03:31.211
I'm retiring.

03:32.246 --> 03:33.074
- Oh, my God!

03:34.835 --> 03:36.285
- Who's gonna take your place?

03:36.319 --> 03:39.253
- As you all know,
Sterling's app ranking

03:39.288 --> 03:40.979
has slipped the last
two months in a row.

03:41.013 --> 03:42.739
That has to change.

03:42.774 --> 03:44.983
We need trend-worthy content.

03:45.017 --> 03:47.434
And the person who
can get me this

03:47.468 --> 03:48.469
will be named

03:49.298 --> 03:52.853
Editor-In-Chief of
Sterling Online.

03:54.061 --> 03:57.858
Shania, Alexa, you two
have been shortlisted.

03:57.892 --> 04:00.101
Get Whitney and
Lydia to help you.

04:00.136 --> 04:02.587
Alexa, I will see
you in my office

04:02.621 --> 04:04.036
tomorrow morning, eight a.m.

04:05.210 --> 04:06.798
Remember,

04:06.832 --> 04:09.110
only one person can win.

04:10.284 --> 04:13.425
[upbeat Indian music]

04:25.437 --> 04:28.198
[car horns beep]

05:13.727 --> 05:17.455
[speaks in foreign language]

05:20.630 --> 05:23.357
- No, I'm still
stuffed from my lunch.

05:23.392 --> 05:27.292
[speaking in foreign language]

05:46.415 --> 05:47.554
No, thank you.

05:51.074 --> 05:54.906
[dispatcher mumbles on radio]

05:57.840 --> 06:01.740
[speaking in foreign language]

06:09.196 --> 06:12.233
Wish we could do some
real police work.

06:12.268 --> 06:15.996
[speaks in foreign language]

06:30.286 --> 06:33.462
- [sighs] Okay, well, Alexa
had some pretty great ideas.

06:33.496 --> 06:35.291
You better be
bringing your A-game.

06:35.325 --> 06:37.293
- Okay, I was thinking,
what about something to do

06:37.327 --> 06:39.433
with the Amish,
like Amish fashion?

06:39.468 --> 06:41.435
- [chuckles] What, like bonnets?

06:41.470 --> 06:43.610
That's not fashion,
that's boring!

06:43.644 --> 06:44.680
Next!

06:44.714 --> 06:46.233
- Okay,

06:46.267 --> 06:50.099
I've got animal prints, I've
got owners and their animals

06:50.133 --> 06:52.860
and the power of blue!

06:52.895 --> 06:54.483
- [Claudia] Mm-mm.

06:54.517 --> 06:55.345
- Oh, yuck!

06:55.380 --> 06:56.588
Don't like my chai cold.

06:56.623 --> 06:57.831
Okay, wait a minute.

06:57.865 --> 06:59.246
What about the way
the 60s designers--

06:59.280 --> 07:02.283
- You know, I was
reading an article

07:02.318 --> 07:04.734
about all the different
ceremonies they have

07:04.769 --> 07:07.047
at Indian weddings, it
was quite fascinating.

07:08.876 --> 07:10.291
Chai's from India, isn't it?

07:11.983 --> 07:13.467
- No, Starbucks.

07:13.502 --> 07:15.400
- You ought to do
a story on that.

07:16.850 --> 07:17.678
- On chai.

07:17.713 --> 07:19.404
- No, India.

07:20.819 --> 07:21.993
- On India!

07:22.027 --> 07:23.719
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

07:23.753 --> 07:25.514
Weddings in India?

07:25.548 --> 07:27.619
I can't think of two
things I hate more!

07:27.654 --> 07:29.345
- Yeah, but you'd
be perfect for it!

07:29.379 --> 07:30.657
- Claudia, I haven't
been to India

07:30.691 --> 07:32.452
since I was six years old.

07:32.486 --> 07:34.005
And I have no desire
to ever go back!

07:34.039 --> 07:35.109
- But you're from India!

07:35.144 --> 07:37.526
- I am from Orange County!

07:37.560 --> 07:40.805
- Listen, India
is hot right now!

07:40.839 --> 07:44.498
Restaurants, movies, call
centers, it's everywhere!

07:44.533 --> 07:48.744
And there are like a billion
Indians, also everywhere.

07:48.778 --> 07:51.988
Think about the billion
people clicking, liking,

07:52.023 --> 07:53.680
sharing, tweeting, trending!

07:53.714 --> 07:55.095
Think about it!

07:55.129 --> 07:57.200
Editor-In-Chief,

07:57.235 --> 07:59.030
Sterling Online,

07:59.064 --> 08:00.687
Shania Dhaliwal!

08:01.722 --> 08:03.759
- Well, you're good.

08:03.793 --> 08:08.660
Sounds terrific, except,
it's not my cup of chai.

08:08.695 --> 08:10.904
- Oh, come on, there's
like a dozen ceremonies.

08:10.938 --> 08:11.974
So much to cover.

08:12.008 --> 08:13.113
- A dozen.

08:13.147 --> 08:14.942
That's 12!
- I tell you what.

08:14.977 --> 08:15.978
You can cover eight.

08:17.945 --> 08:19.222
- Five?

08:19.257 --> 08:20.154
- I can live with that.

08:20.189 --> 08:20.983
Okay!

08:21.017 --> 08:22.950
Five weddings.

08:22.985 --> 08:26.298
Use each wedding to showcase
a different ceremony.

08:26.333 --> 08:28.542
Interview the brides,
do a photo shoot

08:28.577 --> 08:30.958
in some gorgeous
Indian city, yes.

08:30.993 --> 08:32.822
- There's no such thing.

08:32.857 --> 08:34.410
I remember bugs,

08:34.444 --> 08:35.238
bugs,

08:35.273 --> 08:36.654
and bugs.

08:36.688 --> 08:38.656
[sighs] That trip to India

08:38.690 --> 08:40.899
singlehandedly turned
me arachnophobic.

08:40.934 --> 08:41.797
- Oh, come on.

08:41.831 --> 08:42.867
- It's a disability!

08:42.901 --> 08:44.489
- [Claudia] You're going.

08:44.524 --> 08:45.559
[sighs loudly]

08:45.594 --> 08:47.734
[loud knocking]

08:47.768 --> 08:51.703
[speaking in foreign language]

09:19.213 --> 09:22.320
- We really need
to get a promotion.

09:22.354 --> 09:26.704
[old woman speaks
in foreign language]

09:26.738 --> 09:28.533
- Pretending to research
eye covers again?

09:28.568 --> 09:31.432
- Yeah, and you're
interrupting my REM!

09:31.467 --> 09:32.606
- [Shania] Oh,
you gotta help me.

09:32.641 --> 09:33.573
- What's wrong?

09:33.607 --> 09:34.815
Pregnant?
- No!

09:35.678 --> 09:36.610
I might have to go to India!

09:36.645 --> 09:38.163
- What?

09:38.198 --> 09:41.442
- Claudia thinks that that's
gonna be the winning feature.

09:42.478 --> 09:44.687
And you, you gotta help me
come up with another story.

09:44.722 --> 09:46.309
But fast, because
Claudia's already making

09:46.344 --> 09:47.517
all the arrangements.

09:47.552 --> 09:48.760
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, I'm sorry!

09:48.795 --> 09:50.555
So Claudia Burrell, the
woman who's been running

09:50.590 --> 09:52.764
one of the top fashion
magazines for over 20 years

09:52.799 --> 09:55.836
has told you, Shania
Dhaliwal, that if you write

09:55.871 --> 09:57.735
an Indian-themed story,

09:57.769 --> 10:00.841
you may become Editor-In-Chief
of Sterling Online.

10:00.876 --> 10:01.980
- It's about weddings!

10:02.015 --> 10:03.948
But like lots of 'em!
- Right, yeah,

10:03.982 --> 10:05.881
and that's a problem because...

10:05.915 --> 10:07.158
- You know how I
feel about marriage

10:07.192 --> 10:08.642
and you know how I
feel about India.

10:08.677 --> 10:10.540
- And pursuing your dreams?

10:10.575 --> 10:12.301
- I'm arachnophobic.

10:12.335 --> 10:14.406
And India is filled with bugs.

10:14.441 --> 10:15.407
- Are you freakin' kidding me?

10:15.442 --> 10:16.443
You are turning this down

10:16.477 --> 10:17.789
because of a
bug-infested country

10:17.824 --> 10:20.620
that you have to be in for
like a week, two, tops?

10:20.654 --> 10:22.345
[chuckles] Use repellent, woman!

10:22.380 --> 10:24.865
I mean I guess we're taking
orders from Alexa now!

10:26.246 --> 10:28.904
Hey, go where your dad is from.

10:28.938 --> 10:30.112
Remember he used to tell you

10:30.146 --> 10:31.734
about all the places
in his village?

10:32.908 --> 10:34.530
[melancholy music]
- [sighs] Yeah.

10:37.050 --> 10:37.947
- Look, Harbhajan.

10:39.708 --> 10:41.330
I'm sensitive to your problem.

10:42.296 --> 10:43.470
I really am!

10:43.504 --> 10:44.816
Your father was my friend.

10:45.852 --> 10:46.818
He was India's hero.

10:49.718 --> 10:52.341
- Exactly the reason I shouldn't
be doing old folks patrol.

10:54.964 --> 10:57.001
Sir, I know you give me all
these non-risk assignments

10:57.035 --> 10:57.898
because of Mummy Ji.

10:59.037 --> 11:01.453
But this is not the reason
why I joined the police.

11:01.488 --> 11:03.352
It's a big problem for me.

11:03.386 --> 11:05.354
[sighs]

11:09.323 --> 11:11.498
She lost everything when
your dad was killed!

11:12.637 --> 11:13.465
- I understand.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.296
I know she's scared
she'll lose me, too.

11:18.194 --> 11:19.609
But life is not risk-averse.

11:21.335 --> 11:24.166
You know what, that old
biji, she's going to kill me

11:24.200 --> 11:26.996
one of these days with
her stupid jiu jitsu!

11:27.031 --> 11:29.550
[chuckles]

11:29.585 --> 11:32.277
Seriously, sir, I need
something more meaningful.

11:32.312 --> 11:33.796
- [sighs] Harb.

11:35.142 --> 11:37.213
[groans]

11:38.801 --> 11:41.252
How to make your mom
and you happy, eh?

11:44.773 --> 11:47.430
Hmm.

11:53.505 --> 11:54.265
Yeah.

11:56.612 --> 11:58.890
A journalist from Sterling
Magazine in America

11:58.925 --> 12:01.272
has filed visa application,

12:01.306 --> 12:03.067
through the Ministry
of Information.

12:04.378 --> 12:06.760
I know it's not
terrorist with guns

12:07.692 --> 12:10.315
but these foreign journalists
can create enough problems

12:10.350 --> 12:11.282
with the balance.

12:12.317 --> 12:14.319
They all think they
are going to uncover

12:14.354 --> 12:16.666
some big human rights drama,

12:16.701 --> 12:18.841
when they have got plenty
of human rights drama

12:18.876 --> 12:21.326
in their own backyard!

12:21.361 --> 12:22.811
Ministry wants her monitored.

12:24.882 --> 12:27.988
- Yeah, so what do
you want me to do?

12:28.023 --> 12:30.646
- Escort her, be
her liaison officer!

12:30.680 --> 12:32.717
She's coming here to
photograph wedding

12:32.752 --> 12:34.098
and interview brides.

12:34.132 --> 12:35.478
- How hard-hitting.

12:35.513 --> 12:37.273
- One overzealous journalist,

12:38.309 --> 12:40.690
and India's reputation
is at stake.

12:40.725 --> 12:41.519
- These are weddings, sir.

12:41.553 --> 12:42.762
Punjabi weddings.

12:42.796 --> 12:44.625
The only reputation
which is at stake

12:45.799 --> 12:48.181
are actually these
intoxicated baratis.

12:48.215 --> 12:50.666
- [chuckles] Harb,
let's keep it that way!

12:50.700 --> 12:53.186
Just make sure she's staying
within her approvals.

12:54.566 --> 12:58.156
Keep me updated if she deviates
from her research, hmm?

12:58.191 --> 13:00.503
- Does that also
include color patterns

13:00.538 --> 13:02.195
and floral arrangements?

13:02.229 --> 13:03.472
- Sarcasm aside,

13:04.784 --> 13:08.788
Harb, this is an
important assignment.

13:08.822 --> 13:10.997
Or you can go back to
checking on the seniors!

13:13.585 --> 13:15.104
[soft knocking]

13:15.139 --> 13:16.623
- Hi, Mom!
- Hey!

13:18.970 --> 13:20.385
- How are you?

13:20.420 --> 13:22.318
- It's been a long time
since you were in India.

13:22.353 --> 13:24.182
- Oh, and that's
the way I'd like it!

13:28.462 --> 13:30.533
- For sleeping on the plane.

13:30.568 --> 13:32.052
[laughs] Oh, I couldn't help it!

13:32.087 --> 13:32.915
Can't help it!

13:33.813 --> 13:34.434
Okay,

13:34.468 --> 13:35.159
-Hilarious

13:35.193 --> 13:36.574
after the sucker punch!

13:37.609 --> 13:38.438
- Okay.

13:39.611 --> 13:40.509
- Hysterical Love.

13:41.406 --> 13:43.305
- Alright, okay, thank you!

13:45.652 --> 13:47.619
- What are you doing
with my old shirts?

13:47.654 --> 13:48.551
- Oh!

13:48.586 --> 13:49.794
I just wanted to look the part!

13:51.071 --> 13:51.900
Namaste!

13:53.108 --> 13:53.936
- Aww.

13:54.972 --> 13:56.836
These were great times.

14:00.184 --> 14:01.771
- What, you got me
a goodbye present?

14:01.806 --> 14:03.014
I mean, I'm in and I'm out, Ma.

14:03.049 --> 14:04.671
Look at the size of my suitcase.

14:07.018 --> 14:09.710
- No, this is a present
for someone else in India.

14:11.816 --> 14:12.644
- Who?

14:14.474 --> 14:17.546
Corner of Rose Garden,
Old Chandigarh, India?

14:17.580 --> 14:19.755
How the heck am I
supposed to find this?

14:19.789 --> 14:21.999
- [Mom] I'm sure
there's an app for it.

14:22.033 --> 14:25.312
- [laughs] Mom, I'm not FedEx!

14:25.347 --> 14:27.452
- No, of course not,
you're much prettier.

14:32.664 --> 14:34.666
This is for your father.

14:36.392 --> 14:37.221
- What?

14:39.016 --> 14:41.535
We haven't spoken to
Dad since I was six.

14:41.570 --> 14:42.985
And now we're exchanging gifts?

14:43.020 --> 14:45.298
- It's the picture you
snuck out of his suitcase

14:45.332 --> 14:46.816
when he left for India.

14:46.851 --> 14:49.198
And some other pictures of
you, I want him to have them.

14:51.787 --> 14:52.926
- Mom,

14:52.961 --> 14:54.031
no, why?

14:55.204 --> 14:57.689
- Because he asked
for them many times

14:57.724 --> 15:00.278
and I was too
angry to send them.

15:00.313 --> 15:01.210
- Wait.

15:01.245 --> 15:02.936
You've been in touch with him?

15:02.971 --> 15:04.489
- Sort of.

15:04.524 --> 15:07.665
He called, I hung up, he left
messages, I deleted them.

15:08.942 --> 15:10.771
It took me a long time
to get over the fact

15:10.806 --> 15:12.946
that he left just because--
- Mama.

15:12.981 --> 15:14.361
We've been over this.

15:14.396 --> 15:16.260
- And I know that now!

15:16.294 --> 15:17.606
[Shania sighs]

15:17.640 --> 15:19.090
But, Shania, he's a good man.

15:20.540 --> 15:22.922
- A good man would not
leave his family for that.

15:23.853 --> 15:28.375
- Look, he tried to make
it right in so many ways

15:28.410 --> 15:29.480
but I didn't let him.

15:31.654 --> 15:34.071
[sighs] But his last
message was different.

15:35.037 --> 15:36.073
He sounded very sad.

15:38.385 --> 15:41.526
I've forgiven him and I think
you should try, too, as well.

15:45.945 --> 15:49.431
I didn't pack this one but I
think you should have it, too.

15:53.193 --> 15:56.679
- [sighs] Oh, yay,
happily ever after.

15:58.336 --> 15:59.959
Fine.

15:59.993 --> 16:02.892
[melancholy music]

16:12.902 --> 16:15.388
[plane zooms]

16:16.423 --> 16:18.874
- [Woman On PA] Ladies and
gentlemen, welcome to India.

16:18.908 --> 16:21.049
We have landed at
Chandigarh Airport.

16:21.083 --> 16:23.810
I hope you've enjoyed your
flight from New York to Delhi

16:23.844 --> 16:26.123
and we look forward to
serving you in the future.

16:30.127 --> 16:31.645
- [Man On PA] Ladies
and gentlemen,

16:31.680 --> 16:34.648
the flight from Beijing has
landed at New Delhi Airport.

16:34.683 --> 16:38.790
You may collect your
bags at Baggage Claim...

16:38.825 --> 16:42.001
[upbeat Indian music]

16:50.871 --> 16:51.665
[loud squeal]

16:51.700 --> 16:52.528
- What the heck?

16:54.289 --> 16:55.186
I knew I shouldn't have come

16:55.221 --> 16:56.670
to this stupid, stupid country!

16:59.018 --> 17:00.847
Excuse me, sir?

17:00.881 --> 17:02.159
Mister?

17:02.193 --> 17:03.367
Officer!

17:03.401 --> 17:06.059
I was attacked by those people!

17:06.094 --> 17:07.164
Unprovoked, attacked!

17:08.268 --> 17:09.304
You should find them!

17:09.338 --> 17:10.132
You know find?

17:11.720 --> 17:12.755
Do you speak English?

17:13.687 --> 17:15.068
- Find them for what?

17:15.103 --> 17:16.621
To make your clothes
more colorful?

17:16.656 --> 17:17.484
- What?

17:20.246 --> 17:21.454
It's Holi, ma'am.

17:21.488 --> 17:22.972
Festival of Color.

17:23.007 --> 17:24.457
It happens every year.

17:24.491 --> 17:26.183
They're not going to stop
for your arrival, you know.

17:28.944 --> 17:30.601
- Oh, hey!

17:30.635 --> 17:33.224
Hi, are you my liaison officer?

17:33.259 --> 17:35.019
- You are from
Sterling Magazine?

17:35.054 --> 17:36.227
- Yes, yes!

17:36.262 --> 17:37.987
- I'm your tip top
driver, Donald!

17:38.022 --> 17:39.713
Follow me, Madamji, come!
- Okay.

17:40.921 --> 17:41.819
- Come this side!

17:41.853 --> 17:43.441
- Oh, you gotta be kidding me!

17:45.512 --> 17:48.136
I was told you're here
to cover weddings.

17:48.170 --> 17:49.827
And maybe to reconnect
with your Indian roots?

17:49.861 --> 17:51.725
- [scoffs] Well,
you were told wrong.

17:53.727 --> 17:55.281
Wait, why are you following me?

17:56.351 --> 17:58.594
- Sad as it is for both of
us, I'm not following you,

17:58.629 --> 17:59.526
I'm with you.

17:59.561 --> 18:01.390
- What is that supposed to mean?

18:01.425 --> 18:04.773
- I'm Officer Harbhajan
Singh, your liaison officer.

18:04.807 --> 18:06.844
And I can protect you
from those vicious locals

18:06.878 --> 18:08.294
while you're here in India.

18:08.328 --> 18:10.606
- [scoffs] And doing such
a fabulous job of it!

18:10.641 --> 18:12.298
Somebody give this man a raise!

18:14.196 --> 18:17.372
[upbeat Indian music]

18:32.456 --> 18:33.284
- No, thank you.

18:34.458 --> 18:36.253
In India, we stick
to the basics.

18:36.287 --> 18:38.013
You know, good
old-fashioned soap.

18:42.569 --> 18:43.432
- Basics, huh?

18:44.778 --> 18:46.263
How's that workin' out for ya?

18:51.199 --> 18:53.201
I'm sorry, that was really mean.

18:53.235 --> 18:55.168
I shouldn't have said that.

18:55.203 --> 18:56.135
You know what?

18:56.169 --> 18:57.860
The airport was
actually really nice!

18:58.758 --> 18:59.793
- Come, Ms. Dhaliwal.

19:01.450 --> 19:04.798
I'm so glad we did not
disappoint you on all levels.

19:04.833 --> 19:05.661
Thank you.

19:09.562 --> 19:10.321
See?

19:10.356 --> 19:11.150
Over there, cow!

19:12.806 --> 19:14.256
Beautiful, no?

19:14.291 --> 19:15.223
- Yeah,
- Probably 'cause

19:15.257 --> 19:17.156
that's what you think
India's all about!

19:17.190 --> 19:18.502
Right?

19:18.536 --> 19:19.365
- No.

19:19.399 --> 19:20.366
No one ever said that.

19:22.091 --> 19:25.819
Actually, India's changed a
lot since I've been here last.

19:25.854 --> 19:27.511
- India is not a
village anymore.

19:28.097 --> 19:30.859
- Yeah, I've noticed!
- In case you were wondering.

19:30.893 --> 19:31.722
- I see!

19:35.381 --> 19:37.969
Look there, that's like
a family of five there!

19:38.004 --> 19:38.936
- [Harb] What?

19:38.970 --> 19:39.937
Where?

19:39.971 --> 19:41.180
I don't see five.

19:41.214 --> 19:42.974
- What's that one baby
doing on a scooter?

19:43.906 --> 19:46.012
[laughs]

19:50.430 --> 19:53.468
Oh, my God!
- Funny.

19:53.502 --> 19:55.642
- [Shania] So, Donald, is it?

19:55.677 --> 19:57.230
Sounds almost American.

19:57.265 --> 19:59.370
- It is American, Madamji!

19:59.405 --> 20:00.923
I like America!

20:00.958 --> 20:03.616
Madamji, I'm going to
be American someday!

20:03.650 --> 20:06.998
Do you know, Madamji, my
name is Tanweer Singh.

20:07.033 --> 20:09.415
But I call myself Donald!

20:09.449 --> 20:11.727
Like I am in America already!

20:11.762 --> 20:13.488
[chuckles] I have applied

20:13.522 --> 20:16.249
for the green card
lottery nine times!

20:16.284 --> 20:18.389
As my mother used to say,

20:18.424 --> 20:21.668
if you think positive,
it will happen!

20:21.703 --> 20:25.258
One day, I will be in New
York, the Giant Apple!

20:25.293 --> 20:26.915
- Oh no, it's Big Apple.

20:26.949 --> 20:29.642
- The size does not
matter, Madamji!

20:29.676 --> 20:34.163
But first, I must meet
American woman of my dreams!

20:34.198 --> 20:35.268
[loud screaming]

20:35.303 --> 20:36.821
What, what, Madamji?
- Bug, bug!

20:36.856 --> 20:38.271
There, there, there, bug,
bug, bug, please, kill it!

20:38.306 --> 20:40.687
Kill it, kill it, kill
it, bug, bug, bug!

20:40.722 --> 20:42.758
- This one?
- Bug, bug, bug.

20:42.793 --> 20:43.966
- Seriously?
- Bug, bug!

20:44.001 --> 20:46.348
- Okay, okay, okay, okay!

20:46.383 --> 20:47.832
- No, no, no, no, no!

20:47.867 --> 20:49.317
I'm arachnophobic, please,
get that outta here!

20:49.351 --> 20:53.804
Just kill it, kill it,
kill it, kill it, kill it!

20:53.838 --> 20:54.770
- Donald?

20:54.805 --> 20:56.427
[speaking in foreign language]

20:56.462 --> 20:57.290
Pull over.

20:58.533 --> 21:00.776
[groans] Just go,
you little fella!

21:01.743 --> 21:02.916
Fly, fly away!

21:04.504 --> 21:07.645
Done.

21:07.680 --> 21:12.374
Five minutes.

21:12.409 --> 21:13.306
- [Shania] Where you going?

21:13.341 --> 21:17.172
[speaking in foreign language]

21:18.553 --> 21:22.108
Sirji wanted to take you in
gurdwara as a welcome to India!

21:23.316 --> 21:25.145
- You can't be so afraid
of a bitty spider!

21:25.180 --> 21:27.216
- I told you, I'm arachnophobic!

21:28.356 --> 21:29.667
- Arachna-what?

21:29.702 --> 21:31.980
- Afraid of spiders, Daddy!

21:32.014 --> 21:35.017
- Where do you learn such
silly American words?

21:35.052 --> 21:36.467
- Stop, that tickles!

21:36.502 --> 21:38.745
- But I'm a tiny spider
biting your neck!

21:38.780 --> 21:41.265
- [laughs] Mom, Dad's
making fun of my disability!

21:41.300 --> 21:42.370
- What disability?

21:42.404 --> 21:43.405
You're a Sikh!

21:43.440 --> 21:44.441
A warrior!

21:44.475 --> 21:45.787
[growls]

21:45.821 --> 21:46.719
- [laughs] I'm not a warrior!

21:46.753 --> 21:49.860
I'm a princess!
[Dad laughs]

21:55.279 --> 21:59.456
- Madamji, so are you
interested, Madamji?

22:00.733 --> 22:01.699
- What?

22:01.734 --> 22:02.769
Interested?

22:02.804 --> 22:04.012
In what?

22:04.046 --> 22:07.118
- Arranging my marriage
to an American lady!

22:07.153 --> 22:08.741
- Oh!

22:08.775 --> 22:09.983
We don't do that in America.

22:10.018 --> 22:11.744
We don't have
arranged marriages.

22:11.778 --> 22:13.608
- Yes, Madamji, they do!

22:13.642 --> 22:16.783
I have heard of the
Match.com, Plenty of Fish,

22:16.818 --> 22:18.923
JDate, Christian
Mingle, eHarmony,

22:18.958 --> 22:21.995
OkCupid...
- Okay, okay, those are...

22:22.030 --> 22:23.272
It doesn't matter.

22:23.307 --> 22:24.860
I don't know much
about those sites.

22:26.552 --> 22:28.277
I don't ever wanna get married.

22:29.451 --> 22:31.246
- I would be a good husband!

22:31.280 --> 22:35.181
I am funny and I heard
American women like funny!

22:35.215 --> 22:38.357
[upbeat Indian music]

22:48.297 --> 22:50.058
- [Shania] Nice!

22:50.092 --> 22:52.336
- See you can pretend
you're not even in India.

22:54.718 --> 22:56.133
Alright.

22:56.167 --> 22:57.376
I'll see you tomorrow morning?

22:57.410 --> 22:58.204
- Oh, thank you!
- Yeah?

22:58.238 --> 22:59.412
- Yes.

22:59.447 --> 23:00.517
And listen now, here,
before I forget.

23:00.551 --> 23:02.035
Sleep tight,

23:02.070 --> 23:03.623
and don't let the bed bugs bite!

23:05.453 --> 23:07.420
- Wait, there are bugs?

23:10.458 --> 23:12.321
Hey, so I just got to the hotel.

23:12.356 --> 23:13.840
It's lovely!

23:13.875 --> 23:16.015
Outside, a little
bit of everything.

23:16.049 --> 23:18.224
Dirt poor, filthy rich.

23:18.258 --> 23:19.639
I got a list of weddings here.

23:19.674 --> 23:21.952
Quick question, who do
you want me to cover?

23:21.986 --> 23:24.092
- [Claudia Voiceover]
Well, thanks to Hollywood,

23:24.126 --> 23:27.440
we've seen slumdogs
and millionaires.

23:27.475 --> 23:28.993
Why don't you cover
the real India?

23:29.028 --> 23:30.443
The one in between?

23:30.478 --> 23:32.583
You know, middle India.

23:32.618 --> 23:36.932
[upbeat Indian music on TV]

23:36.967 --> 23:38.244
- Mummy Ji!

23:38.278 --> 23:39.210
- [Mamiji] Mm!

23:39.245 --> 23:40.384
Stuck on work again?

23:41.903 --> 23:43.491
Just like your father.

23:43.525 --> 23:44.423
- [Harb] Starving.

23:46.908 --> 23:48.323
- He never got home on time.

23:57.850 --> 23:59.403
So,

23:59.438 --> 24:00.266
what kept you?

24:01.509 --> 24:02.786
- An American girl.
- Mm!

24:03.614 --> 24:07.376
I saw on the news an
American attacked a Sikh,

24:07.411 --> 24:09.171
thinking he was a Muslim!

24:09.206 --> 24:11.519
No concept of other
culture, these Americans!

24:12.692 --> 24:15.626
- I'm sure not all of
them are like that, hmm?

24:15.661 --> 24:17.732
- Americans see a
turban and they think

24:17.766 --> 24:19.250
there is a bomb in it!

24:19.285 --> 24:21.529
- And how do you know
so much about Americans?

24:21.563 --> 24:22.599
You've never even
been to America.

24:22.633 --> 24:24.739
- I have seen Hollywood movies.

24:24.773 --> 24:27.396
- You and your
Hollywood and Bollywood.

24:27.431 --> 24:28.501
Why do you watch such drivel?

24:28.536 --> 24:30.261
- It makes me feel!
- Nauseous.

24:31.435 --> 24:34.024
- [sighs] Anything fun
makes you nauseous.

24:34.058 --> 24:36.854
No girlfriend, no wife, no love.

24:36.889 --> 24:39.547
[speaks in foreign language]

24:39.581 --> 24:40.996
- The American girl is cute.

24:43.171 --> 24:44.413
[Mamiji sighs]

24:44.448 --> 24:48.279
[mobile phone rings]

24:48.314 --> 24:49.971
- [Whitney] It's me!

24:50.005 --> 24:52.180
- My God, I'm so
glad you called!

24:52.214 --> 24:53.561
- Yeah, what's goin' on?

24:53.595 --> 24:54.769
Hey, how was the flight?

24:54.803 --> 24:55.666
- Flight was good.

24:55.701 --> 24:57.357
The ride to the hotel?

24:57.392 --> 24:58.497
Not so good.

24:58.531 --> 25:00.015
How's work?

25:00.050 --> 25:01.845
- Well, talk about not so
good entertaining clients.

25:01.879 --> 25:03.329
You know how much I hate that!

25:03.363 --> 25:05.469
- Oh, yeah, I know.

25:05.504 --> 25:06.815
- Okay, okay, so wait a second.

25:06.850 --> 25:08.334
What's happening with your dad?

25:08.368 --> 25:10.819
- [Shania] [sighs]
I don't know, Whit.

25:10.854 --> 25:12.925
Honestly, I should
just mail it to him.

25:14.098 --> 25:17.377
A part of me, I really
wanna see him again.

25:20.484 --> 25:25.489
[upbeat Indian music]
[horns beep]

26:01.767 --> 26:03.182
- Good morning, Madamji!

26:03.216 --> 26:04.666
You look so lovely this morning!

26:04.701 --> 26:06.288
- Aww, you're so sweet!

26:09.188 --> 26:10.465
Good morning!

26:12.053 --> 26:12.881
- Good morning.

26:18.577 --> 26:20.337
- So you like the decorations?

26:20.371 --> 26:23.547
I did the flags to
make you feel at home!

26:24.444 --> 26:26.446
It's very American, no?

26:26.481 --> 26:29.795
I try to find American
flags made in America

26:30.968 --> 26:34.247
but the closest I
could get was China.

26:34.282 --> 26:35.628
- I like it, Donald.

26:35.663 --> 26:37.561
I give you an A for effort.

26:37.596 --> 26:39.598
- I don't mean to correct you.

26:39.632 --> 26:41.461
But A is for alpha.

26:41.496 --> 26:46.121
You see, effort start with E!
[mobile phone rings]

26:46.156 --> 26:48.399
- Hey, Mark!
- Hehehey, beautiful!

26:49.366 --> 26:51.161
I sure miss that face.

26:51.195 --> 26:52.334
- What's up?

26:52.369 --> 26:53.266
- You're never
gonna believe this.

26:53.301 --> 26:54.336
Your photographer is sick.

26:54.371 --> 26:56.649
He's stuck in Delhi and
can't get on his flight.

26:56.684 --> 26:57.616
- This can't be happening!

26:57.650 --> 26:59.031
I need another photographer!

26:59.065 --> 27:00.411
- Well, I can look
in the database.

27:00.446 --> 27:01.585
- Madamji!

27:01.620 --> 27:03.622
Madamji, Madamji!
- Would they be under F

27:03.656 --> 27:05.451
for photographer?
- Madamji, Madamji!

27:05.485 --> 27:07.246
- Hold on, Donald,
what is it, what?

27:07.280 --> 27:10.421
- I know a tiptop photographer
who lives in Chandigarh!

27:10.456 --> 27:11.837
- Oh, my gosh,
you know somebody?

27:11.871 --> 27:12.907
- Yes, Madamji!

27:12.941 --> 27:14.391
First class photographer!

27:14.425 --> 27:15.668
- Okay, Mark.

27:15.703 --> 27:17.359
The driver could give me
a photographer for today

27:17.394 --> 27:19.707
but you have to get me another
one for the next wedding.

27:21.260 --> 27:22.571
[Mark mumbles]

27:22.606 --> 27:23.780
Gotta go, bye.

27:23.814 --> 27:24.919
- Love it when you
boss me around!

27:28.957 --> 27:30.856
[clears throat]

27:30.890 --> 27:33.168
- He seems to be a real keeper.

27:34.860 --> 27:37.690
- Well, at least the phone
reception was working.

27:37.725 --> 27:38.587
- Oh, yeah.

27:40.279 --> 27:42.005
We all share one
broken down satellite

27:42.039 --> 27:44.939
to serve the 1.3 billion
people of the entire country.

27:48.218 --> 27:49.806
- Oh, my God.

27:49.840 --> 27:51.428
All of you share one satellite?

27:54.362 --> 27:55.674
- Can I tell you one secret?

27:57.537 --> 28:00.506
Actually they are just
pretending to talk on the phone.

28:00.540 --> 28:02.611
Nobody's talking to anyone.

28:02.646 --> 28:03.474
- What?

28:06.512 --> 28:08.479
[sighs]

28:08.514 --> 28:11.137
[soft laughing]

28:14.969 --> 28:18.420
[uplifting Indian music]

28:24.323 --> 28:26.912
[people cheer]

28:34.782 --> 28:35.921
Ugh, a puddle.

28:37.336 --> 28:38.751
- [Donald] Oh,
Parveen, my friend!

28:38.786 --> 28:41.202
- Hello, hello, hello!

28:41.236 --> 28:43.687
- [Shania] [squeals
softly] What are you doing?

28:43.722 --> 28:45.171
- [Harbhajan] [groans] You
were going to have a problem

28:45.206 --> 28:46.483
with the puddle,

28:46.517 --> 28:48.381
I was going to have a problem
with you having a problem,

28:48.416 --> 28:50.487
so now I'm avoiding
myriad of problems.

28:50.521 --> 28:51.764
You have a problem with that?

28:51.799 --> 28:53.939
- [Shania] No! [laughs]

28:53.973 --> 28:55.078
Ok, thank you!

28:55.112 --> 28:56.596
- Here you are
photographer, Madamji!

28:56.631 --> 28:57.874
Parveen, my friend!

28:57.908 --> 29:00.324
- Hello, I'm Shania
from Sterling Magazine!

29:00.359 --> 29:02.706
- Hello, Ji, hello! [speaks
in foreign language]

29:02.741 --> 29:03.638
- [Shania] Thank you!

29:03.672 --> 29:04.881
- That is my work.

29:06.020 --> 29:09.437
[people singing faintly]

29:10.507 --> 29:12.060
- [Shania] What exactly
am I looking at?

29:12.095 --> 29:16.099
- That is my, how you say
in America, my portfolio!

29:16.133 --> 29:17.445
My portfolio!

29:17.479 --> 29:18.964
- What did I tell you, Madamji?

29:18.998 --> 29:21.311
Best photographer in
all of Chandigarh!

29:21.345 --> 29:24.141
Not Chandigarh, all
of India! [chuckles]

29:24.176 --> 29:25.418
- Oh! [chuckles weakly]

29:25.453 --> 29:26.626
- So you like this?
- Yeah, sure, sure.

29:26.661 --> 29:30.769
- [Donald] Ok! [speaks
in foreign language]

29:32.391 --> 29:37.396
[rhythmic drum music]
[women clapping]

29:53.343 --> 29:56.001
[women singing]

30:05.182 --> 30:07.253
- Oh, hi, Shania!

30:07.288 --> 30:08.703
How are you?
- Hello!

30:08.737 --> 30:10.153
- Oh, sorry, I have
Mehndi all over!

30:10.187 --> 30:11.188
Please, please come!

30:12.465 --> 30:14.329
Have a seat!

30:14.364 --> 30:16.055
- [Shania] Hello!
[women greet loudly]

30:16.090 --> 30:17.919
Hi, hello, hello!

30:17.954 --> 30:19.265
Hi, hello!

30:19.300 --> 30:20.888
- So how are you?
- Good, how are you?

30:20.922 --> 30:23.028
- I am enjoying my day!

30:23.062 --> 30:25.064
- Yes, thank you for
having me, Devika!

30:25.099 --> 30:27.480
- You're welcome!
- Ok, one second.

30:27.515 --> 30:29.724
Wedding number one,
Mehndi ceremony,

30:29.758 --> 30:32.589
better known as the
henna tattoo in the west.

30:32.623 --> 30:35.350
- This is the bridal shower
like you have in the US.

30:35.385 --> 30:36.869
- 'Kay.

30:36.904 --> 30:39.665
- And we are doing the Mehndi
ceremony like tattoo for you

30:39.699 --> 30:43.186
but tradition for us, so
make the bride look beautiful

30:43.220 --> 30:46.085
on her special day
so how's it looking?

30:46.120 --> 30:47.052
- Beautiful!

30:47.086 --> 30:48.329
- [Devika] Would you
like to have some made?

30:48.363 --> 30:49.986
- Oh, maybe later!

30:50.020 --> 30:52.402
Devika, can you tell us a
little bit more about this?

30:52.436 --> 30:54.300
- Yeah, there are
ceremonies like Mehndi

30:54.335 --> 30:56.026
and then Ladies Sangeet and...

30:56.061 --> 30:57.338
[woman shouts in
foreign language]

30:57.372 --> 30:59.616
Ooh, ooh, hijras,
hijras are here!

30:59.650 --> 31:02.999
[hijras chant in
foreign language]

31:03.033 --> 31:05.139
Let me tell you about hijras.

31:05.173 --> 31:08.176
Hijras, they come, they find
out where the wedding is

31:08.211 --> 31:10.316
and show up and bless the bride.

31:10.351 --> 31:11.870
- [Shania] Oh, wow!

31:11.904 --> 31:16.115
[hijras chant in
foreign language]

31:18.807 --> 31:19.912
Who are they?

31:19.947 --> 31:20.740
- Hijras.

31:20.775 --> 31:21.603
- [Shania] Hija-what?

31:22.811 --> 31:24.399
- Transvestite, transgenders.

31:25.573 --> 31:26.677
Eunuchs?

31:26.712 --> 31:29.473
- [Shania] Oh, right.

31:29.508 --> 31:32.752
[hijra speaks in
foreign language]

31:32.787 --> 31:33.995
- They just find out
where the wedding is

31:34.030 --> 31:36.032
and they just show up.
- Oh.

31:36.066 --> 31:37.688
Where the heck's Parveen?

31:38.620 --> 31:39.863
Hey, Parveen!

31:39.898 --> 31:42.521
- Oh, sorry, sorry!

31:42.555 --> 31:44.868
[speaks in foreign language]

31:44.903 --> 31:46.180
- [Hijras] Media!

31:46.214 --> 31:47.595
- No media!

31:47.629 --> 31:49.562
I'm from Sterling
Magazine from America!

31:49.597 --> 31:51.806
- Oh, okay!
- Smile, please, smile!

31:51.840 --> 31:53.187
Smile!
- Can we ask you

31:53.221 --> 31:54.602
some questions?
- Yes, of course.

31:54.636 --> 31:57.018
- Okay, okay, no questions,
please, thank you.

31:57.053 --> 31:57.985
Okay, we're done here.

31:58.019 --> 31:58.951
Thank you, you guys can go out.

31:58.986 --> 32:00.159
Thank you, go on.

32:00.194 --> 32:02.334
- You can see, people
want our blessings

32:02.368 --> 32:03.576
but they treat us like a curse.

32:03.611 --> 32:05.061
This is very bad.
- Alright, thank you,

32:05.095 --> 32:06.476
move out!
- Very bad!

32:06.510 --> 32:08.857
Ma'am, this is
how they treat us.

32:08.892 --> 32:09.824
- Out!

32:09.858 --> 32:11.239
- Very, very bad!
- Out, out, thank you.

32:11.274 --> 32:13.379
Thank you, out, out, out, out.

32:13.414 --> 32:14.933
Sorry, guys, sorry, sorry.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.314
I mean girls.

32:17.349 --> 32:18.350
I'm just doing my job.

32:19.282 --> 32:20.145
I'm really sorry!

32:27.014 --> 32:28.394
- What do they mean by that?

32:29.568 --> 32:30.879
Why didn't you let
