49:58.340 --> 49:59.755
What did you mean?

49:59.789 --> 50:01.826
- We are a dirty little secret.

50:01.860 --> 50:02.792
- Move!

50:02.827 --> 50:03.655
Sit over there!

50:07.280 --> 50:08.867
- Dirty little...

50:08.902 --> 50:09.730
What do you mean?

50:11.663 --> 50:15.702
- The soul of a woman
trapped in the body of a man.

50:15.736 --> 50:16.806
- [Policeman] Silence!

50:16.841 --> 50:18.049
Go in cell!

50:18.084 --> 50:19.878
Go!

50:19.913 --> 50:23.158
- In India, sometimes
people get born with no...

50:23.192 --> 50:24.090
- Go, go!
- Move.

50:26.402 --> 50:27.231
Go!

50:28.715 --> 50:31.373
[loud creaking]

50:33.996 --> 50:38.069
[police siren wails faintly]

50:38.104 --> 50:39.519
- Sharmila?
- Here.

50:40.727 --> 50:43.661
- So did you mean born
with no sexual organs?

50:43.695 --> 50:45.111
- Yes.

50:45.145 --> 50:47.389
- Well, why is that
a dirty secret?

50:47.423 --> 50:49.805
If you feel your soul
is a woman's soul,

50:50.840 --> 50:51.807
then you're a woman.

50:53.050 --> 50:54.258
- You lose your soul

50:55.776 --> 51:00.264
because our parents gives
you up to the hijra community

51:00.298 --> 51:01.782
because you are not normal

51:02.680 --> 51:04.337
and they could all
ties after that.

51:05.752 --> 51:08.341
- Oh, so that's how
you become a hijra.

51:08.375 --> 51:09.687
- That,

51:09.721 --> 51:11.275
and forced castration.

51:12.517 --> 51:14.381
[police shouts in
foreign language]

51:14.416 --> 51:17.074
[loud rattling]

51:19.731 --> 51:21.561
- I made a friend last night.

51:21.595 --> 51:24.046
And you're never
gonna believe who.

51:24.081 --> 51:25.875
- You have no friends in India.

51:25.910 --> 51:27.084
- Good morning, Madamji.

51:28.326 --> 51:30.328
[car horns beep faintly]

51:30.363 --> 51:32.158
- You're my friend,
right, Donald?

51:32.192 --> 51:33.435
- Yes, Madamji.

51:33.469 --> 51:35.161
Very much so!
- See?

51:35.195 --> 51:36.610
I do have a friend in India.

51:40.580 --> 51:42.685
Look, I'm really sorry.

51:44.239 --> 51:46.482
Thank you for getting me out.

51:46.517 --> 51:47.725
If you would've left me there,

51:47.759 --> 51:49.347
I don't know what
I would've done.

51:51.004 --> 51:53.903
[melancholy music]

51:58.563 --> 52:01.877
[keyboard clacking]

52:01.911 --> 52:03.465
- Whew, okay!

52:03.499 --> 52:05.087
How about this.

52:05.122 --> 52:07.710
"Dear Mr. Commissioner, my
name is Whitney Simmons."

52:08.918 --> 52:12.370
- "I am a colleague
of Shania Dhaliwal

52:12.405 --> 52:15.062
"from Sterling Magazine."

52:15.097 --> 52:17.203
- "Who's in India
writing a story.

52:17.237 --> 52:19.653
"And I wanted to get your
comment on the sidebar

52:19.688 --> 52:22.000
"she is writing on the hijras."

52:22.035 --> 52:24.382
I don't even know if
that's how you say it.

52:25.418 --> 52:26.867
[faint Indian music]

52:26.902 --> 52:28.352
- Sidebar on hijras?

52:29.974 --> 52:31.700
- Are you sure we
should be doing this?

52:31.734 --> 52:33.840
- Oh, come on, don't be lame.

52:34.806 --> 52:37.913
[phone beeps softly]

52:39.259 --> 52:42.538
[subdued Indian music]

53:04.042 --> 53:05.320
- Good morning.

53:05.354 --> 53:07.184
- Good morning, Madamji.
- Good morning, Donald!

53:07.218 --> 53:08.840
- You look so nice
in Indian dress!

53:08.875 --> 53:11.671
- Thank you, let's see what
the other officer has to say!

53:13.707 --> 53:15.226
Good mo--

53:15.261 --> 53:16.158
You are?

53:16.193 --> 53:19.334
- I'm Officer Chahel.

53:19.368 --> 53:22.647
[subdued Indian music]

53:34.141 --> 53:36.972
- Not that it matters, but
what happened to Harbhajan?

53:37.006 --> 53:38.939
- I don't know, Madamji.

53:38.974 --> 53:42.080
Sirji said he's taking
himself off the assignment.

53:45.394 --> 53:46.671
Are you okay, Madamji?

53:46.706 --> 53:47.914
- Of course.

53:47.948 --> 53:48.846
Why wouldn't I be?

53:50.296 --> 53:53.644
I mean, he's a grown man, he
could do what he wants, right?

53:55.128 --> 53:57.993
Besides, Chahel
seems way more fun.

53:59.408 --> 54:00.996
Right, Chahel?

54:01.030 --> 54:02.446
- Chahel.

54:02.480 --> 54:04.241
Cha, Cha, Chahel.

54:05.380 --> 54:07.692
- [chuckles] Oh,
like dance, cha-cha!

54:07.727 --> 54:09.349
[horn beeps loudly]

54:09.384 --> 54:12.076
Ooh-kay, then. [sighs]

54:14.423 --> 54:16.736
Oh, that's where I got
arrested the other night!

54:23.846 --> 54:25.434
Hey, are you married?

54:25.469 --> 54:26.297
- No.

54:28.437 --> 54:30.508
- What a surprise.

54:30.543 --> 54:33.546
[upbeat band music]

54:39.517 --> 54:42.209
[camera clicks]

54:58.191 --> 55:02.195
[men chant in foreign language]

55:19.074 --> 55:22.388
[tranquil Indian music]

56:18.271 --> 56:22.586
[priest chants in
foreign language]

56:30.283 --> 56:34.529
[hijras speak in
foreign language]

56:40.051 --> 56:40.949
- Hello!

56:40.983 --> 56:42.744
Is Sharmila, where's Sharmila?

56:42.778 --> 56:43.607
No!

56:45.609 --> 56:49.544
[speaking in foreign language]

56:51.925 --> 56:53.133
- Go, go!

56:53.168 --> 56:54.652
Go, go!

56:54.687 --> 56:56.551
- Google!

56:56.585 --> 56:58.449
- [speaks in foreign
language] Thank you very much

56:58.484 --> 57:00.486
for coming!
- Thank you.

57:00.520 --> 57:03.316
Could you tell me
about the Anand?

57:03.350 --> 57:04.800
- Anand Karaj.
- Mm.

57:04.835 --> 57:06.457
- And Doli.
- Yes.

57:06.492 --> 57:10.427
- Anand Karaj is our
version of your church.

57:11.462 --> 57:12.429
And the Doli,

57:13.499 --> 57:14.810
goodbye to her.

57:16.812 --> 57:17.641
It was only

57:19.021 --> 57:21.576
yesterday when I was cradling

57:21.610 --> 57:24.233
my little daughter

57:24.268 --> 57:25.096
in my arm.

57:26.408 --> 57:27.892
And

57:27.927 --> 57:31.171
she has grown up. [sniffs]

57:31.206 --> 57:33.795
It goes so fast! [sobs]

57:33.829 --> 57:36.142
She is going away from us!

57:37.074 --> 57:38.144
- Oh, how far away?

57:40.146 --> 57:41.561
- Just down the street.

57:43.321 --> 57:45.323
[melancholy music]
Father and daughter

57:45.358 --> 57:47.394
always a special bond.

57:49.224 --> 57:52.399
She's always
father's little girl.

57:53.849 --> 57:55.713
[melancholy music]

57:55.748 --> 57:59.614
[speaking in foreign language]

57:59.648 --> 58:04.653
[upbeat Indian music]
[children shout]

58:06.655 --> 58:08.830
- Hello, Madamji!
- Hello, Madamji!

58:08.864 --> 58:10.521
- Hi!
- Sharmila house?

58:10.556 --> 58:11.764
- Yes!

58:11.798 --> 58:13.075
- This one, Sharmila house.
- Thank you!

58:13.110 --> 58:13.938
- Sharmila house!

58:19.323 --> 58:20.220
- Oh, my God!

58:20.255 --> 58:21.946
Are you okay?

58:21.981 --> 58:23.465
- By the grace of God,

58:24.501 --> 58:26.088
just some bruises.

58:26.123 --> 58:27.365
- What happened?

58:27.400 --> 58:29.747
- Well, I took your advice.

58:30.645 --> 58:32.370
I went to a local store

58:33.233 --> 58:34.062
for a job.

58:35.132 --> 58:36.443
They laughed at me.

58:37.790 --> 58:38.860
I got angry.

58:40.240 --> 58:42.380
- Did you threaten to
take your clothes off?

58:42.415 --> 58:43.243
- [chuckles] No.

58:44.486 --> 58:45.901
I threatened to beat him.
- No.

58:46.799 --> 58:48.835
- Except he get me first.

58:50.216 --> 58:52.183
Do people beat reporters?

58:53.219 --> 58:55.117
- Are you kidding?

58:55.152 --> 58:56.429
We're universally loved.

59:00.295 --> 59:02.435
- Thanks for trying
to help me, Madamji.

59:04.437 --> 59:06.750
- Did you report
this to the police?

59:06.784 --> 59:09.235
- What's the point, Madamji?

59:09.269 --> 59:11.444
It is the way our world works.

59:12.618 --> 59:16.173
- Sharmila, we have
to tell your story.

59:16.207 --> 59:18.002
- I'm a simple girl, Madamji.

59:19.003 --> 59:21.488
No one wants to know my story.

59:21.523 --> 59:24.422
- That's exactly why people
do wanna know your story.

59:26.908 --> 59:29.048
[soft knocking]

59:29.082 --> 59:29.911
- Sir?

59:35.330 --> 59:37.435
I thought she was doing
an article on weddings.

59:37.470 --> 59:39.058
- Precisely.

59:39.092 --> 59:39.886
Sit!

59:44.546 --> 59:46.030
Harbhajan,

59:46.065 --> 59:49.516
Ministry approved her to
do a feature on weddings.

59:49.551 --> 59:51.657
This was not part
of her application.

59:51.691 --> 59:53.866
She has to respect our rules!

59:53.900 --> 59:55.315
If she continues,

59:55.350 --> 59:57.732
I have an order to confiscate
Ms. Dhaliwal's computer.

59:57.766 --> 59:58.940
- But those are the
personal possessions

59:58.974 --> 1:00:00.286
of an undetained individual.

1:00:00.320 --> 1:00:02.460
- And that undetained
individual thinks

1:00:02.495 --> 1:00:04.946
she can break the rules
or do whatever she wants?

1:00:07.673 --> 1:00:08.501
Look,

1:00:09.640 --> 1:00:11.159
if you are not
morally up for it,

1:00:14.852 --> 1:00:17.614
my only choice is to assign
another officer to it.

1:00:19.650 --> 1:00:22.964
[phone clicks]

1:00:22.998 --> 1:00:23.999
Who are you texting?

1:00:25.414 --> 1:00:28.383
- I'm just telling Mom that
I'll be late for dinner

1:00:28.417 --> 1:00:30.488
and that I'm still
on the assignment.

1:00:30.523 --> 1:00:31.317
- Mm, good.

1:00:33.768 --> 1:00:35.217
- I'll make sure.

1:00:35.252 --> 1:00:36.080
- Better.

1:00:37.426 --> 1:00:39.774
- [Shania Voiceover]
Hijras, blessings for some,

1:00:39.808 --> 1:00:40.637
curse for all.

1:00:41.845 --> 1:00:44.192
As I left my new friend
still freshly bruised...

1:00:44.226 --> 1:00:46.712
[phone beeps]

1:00:50.198 --> 1:00:52.027
I couldn't help but
wonder how a community

1:00:52.062 --> 1:00:55.306
that has references in the
Mahabharata for their good luck

1:00:55.341 --> 1:00:57.757
now can't even get
a job as basic help.

1:00:57.792 --> 1:01:00.070
Ultimate goal for all hijras:

1:01:00.104 --> 1:01:03.694
The world doesn't have to accept
us but they can respect us.

1:01:06.490 --> 1:01:09.182
[relaxing music]

1:01:11.737 --> 1:01:12.910
[speaks in foreign language]

1:01:12.945 --> 1:01:14.429
- You look very
pretty, very pretty!

1:01:14.463 --> 1:01:17.328
- Oh, thank you! [chuckles]

1:01:19.986 --> 1:01:20.987
Where have you been?

1:01:21.816 --> 1:01:22.679
- I was off grid.

1:01:25.198 --> 1:01:27.338
- And what did you mean
by that text you sent?

1:01:28.546 --> 1:01:30.652
- Just a reminder
to stay focused.

1:01:30.687 --> 1:01:33.103
Try and get approval
for the hijra story,

1:01:33.137 --> 1:01:34.725
and got you an application form.

1:01:34.760 --> 1:01:35.415
- [Shania] Oh, yeah?

1:01:35.450 --> 1:01:37.245
And what if they reject it?

1:01:37.279 --> 1:01:39.005
- Listen, Shania--
- Oh, my God,

1:01:39.040 --> 1:01:42.250
there is no article on hijras!

1:01:42.284 --> 1:01:43.458
So I'm kind of lost!

1:01:45.184 --> 1:01:46.841
- You seem to lose
your way a lot.

1:01:46.875 --> 1:01:47.738
- Do I really?

1:01:47.773 --> 1:01:48.635
- Oh, yes!

1:01:50.051 --> 1:01:51.397
And you're quite a handful.

1:01:52.294 --> 1:01:53.571
- So why'd you come back?

1:01:56.540 --> 1:01:58.128
- Sometimes I like
my hands full!

1:01:59.957 --> 1:02:04.928
[chuckles]
[upbeat Indian music]

1:02:18.182 --> 1:02:20.495
- Hello, Ms.
Dhaliwal, I presume?

1:02:20.529 --> 1:02:22.152
- Hello!
- Hi, I'm Harleen,

1:02:22.186 --> 1:02:24.464
the bride of the wedding
and this is Mr. [mumbles],

1:02:24.499 --> 1:02:25.603
my husband.
- Nice to meet you.

1:02:25.638 --> 1:02:26.777
Thank you so much

1:02:26.812 --> 1:02:28.020
for having us!
- Thank you so much!

1:02:28.054 --> 1:02:29.780
I suppose you're here
to cover the wedding?

1:02:29.815 --> 1:02:30.781
- Yes, yes.
- That's great!

1:02:30.816 --> 1:02:32.162
- May I ask you some questions?

1:02:32.196 --> 1:02:33.991
- Yeah, why not, go ahead.

1:02:34.026 --> 1:02:36.960
- Okay, so can you tell
me about this ceremony?

1:02:36.994 --> 1:02:39.134
- Yes, well, this
is the reception.

1:02:40.860 --> 1:02:42.966
- Is there another
word in Punjabi?

1:02:43.000 --> 1:02:46.279
- [chuckles] Reception is the
Punjabi word for reception.

1:02:46.314 --> 1:02:47.936
- Well, your English
is really great.

1:02:47.971 --> 1:02:49.317
- [Bhavna] Hi, Shaniaji!

1:02:49.351 --> 1:02:51.215
- Oh, Bhavna, what
are you doing here?

1:02:51.250 --> 1:02:53.770
- Shaniaji, Harleen and
me are very good friends.

1:02:53.804 --> 1:02:56.496
- And you know what, she
is getting married soon!

1:02:56.531 --> 1:02:58.084
- You're getting
married to the American!

1:02:58.119 --> 1:02:59.327
- No!

1:02:59.361 --> 1:03:00.811
No, I'm not going to
Alabama, my Shania ji.

1:03:01.950 --> 1:03:04.677
Actually, my Papaji
made the choice for me.

1:03:04.711 --> 1:03:07.956
And he chose my
happiness over history.

1:03:07.991 --> 1:03:09.544
So surprise for you!

1:03:09.578 --> 1:03:11.097
Salman!

1:03:11.132 --> 1:03:14.549
- Oh, wow, Cookies and Cream!
- [giggles] Yes!

1:03:14.583 --> 1:03:16.516
- That's wonderful!
- This all happened

1:03:16.551 --> 1:03:17.966
only because of you, Shaniaji.

1:03:18.001 --> 1:03:20.072
- Cookies and Cream
is back, baby!

1:03:20.106 --> 1:03:21.590
- Yeah! [laughs]

1:03:21.625 --> 1:03:24.317
Shaniaji, you know what,
when we both get married,

1:03:24.352 --> 1:03:26.837
you have to be the
bride's friend, hmm?

1:03:26.872 --> 1:03:27.942
- Bride's friend.

1:03:27.976 --> 1:03:29.806
The bridesmaid, yes.
- See you!

1:03:29.840 --> 1:03:30.807
- She's funny, come!

1:03:30.841 --> 1:03:32.291
- Very funny.
- Let's enjoy.

1:03:32.325 --> 1:03:33.188
- Testing, testing.

1:03:33.223 --> 1:03:34.155
Hanji, hanji!

1:03:34.189 --> 1:03:37.089
[loud thuds]
Hello, hello.

1:03:37.123 --> 1:03:40.299
[upbeat Indian music]

1:05:31.928 --> 1:05:33.343
- [Harbhajan] Cookies and
Cream getting married.

1:05:33.377 --> 1:05:35.448
[chuckles] Amazing.

1:05:35.483 --> 1:05:37.347
Well, there's your fifth
wedding.

1:05:37.381 --> 1:05:38.935
- [Shania] Yeah.

1:05:38.969 --> 1:05:40.798
- Come on, you should
be over the moon now.

1:05:50.325 --> 1:05:53.570
- I have to get this
package to my dad

1:05:53.604 --> 1:05:56.090
but I have no idea how to
find this crazy address.

1:06:02.613 --> 1:06:04.512
- Your dad's in Chandigarh?

1:06:04.546 --> 1:06:05.720
- Yeah.

1:06:05.754 --> 1:06:06.652
It's a long story.

1:06:07.964 --> 1:06:09.758
It's time to write
the next chapter.

1:06:10.794 --> 1:06:12.485
Will you help me?

1:06:12.520 --> 1:06:14.384
[car horn beeps]

1:06:14.418 --> 1:06:17.145
- [chuckles] We're
not even dating

1:06:17.180 --> 1:06:18.698
and I get to meet your father.

1:06:20.183 --> 1:06:22.461
[chuckles]

1:06:23.289 --> 1:06:24.808
Are we ready for that?

1:06:26.741 --> 1:06:30.055
[relaxing Indian music]

1:07:10.992 --> 1:07:12.200
- [Shania] Oh, my God.

1:07:12.235 --> 1:07:13.822
I wonder if he'll
even recognize me.

1:07:15.100 --> 1:07:17.309
Harb, I can't do this!

1:07:17.343 --> 1:07:19.863
- Oh, come on.
- Oh, my gosh!

1:07:19.897 --> 1:07:23.211
[relaxing Indian music]

1:07:28.596 --> 1:07:31.668
[soft knocking]

1:07:31.702 --> 1:07:35.603
[speaking in foreign language]

1:07:41.505 --> 1:07:44.612
[bell tolls faintly]

1:07:52.137 --> 1:07:56.072
[speaking in foreign language]

1:08:14.055 --> 1:08:17.196
[melancholy music]

1:08:17.231 --> 1:08:18.301
- Hey, I'm...

1:08:19.647 --> 1:08:20.475
I'm sorry.

1:08:22.960 --> 1:08:24.617
I know how it feels.

1:08:26.999 --> 1:08:28.725
I've been there.

1:08:28.759 --> 1:08:30.761
[sighs]

1:08:40.530 --> 1:08:43.774
[wistful Indian music]

1:09:17.946 --> 1:09:20.017
- [Little Shania] Daddy,
what happens when you die?

1:09:20.052 --> 1:09:20.880
- Mm!

1:09:21.743 --> 1:09:23.469
Well, we reincarnate!

1:09:25.057 --> 1:09:29.165
The soul comes back
as something different

1:09:29.199 --> 1:09:30.959
to be with who we love.

1:09:30.994 --> 1:09:33.341
- How do you know
the soul's back?

1:09:33.376 --> 1:09:35.861
- If you look really
hard, you'll see it.

1:09:35.895 --> 1:09:38.243
- When you die will
your soul come back?

1:09:38.277 --> 1:09:41.315
- [laughs] Only for you!

1:09:41.349 --> 1:09:43.179
- What if I don't
look hard enough,

1:09:43.213 --> 1:09:45.146
then I won't know it's you.

1:09:45.181 --> 1:09:46.285
- Hmm.

1:09:46.320 --> 1:09:47.735
Tell you what.

1:09:47.769 --> 1:09:50.255
I'll come back as

1:09:50.289 --> 1:09:51.808
a pigeon!

1:09:51.842 --> 1:09:53.361
- [Little Shania] A pigeon?

1:09:53.396 --> 1:09:58.401
- [Rajinder] Mm-hm.

1:10:13.036 --> 1:10:14.762
- Here?

1:10:14.796 --> 1:10:17.351
Better?
- Mm-hm.

1:10:17.385 --> 1:10:20.630
[wistful Indian music]

1:10:25.704 --> 1:10:26.912
Wow.

1:10:26.946 --> 1:10:28.672
Can't believe I'll
never see him again.

1:10:33.781 --> 1:10:36.922
Anyway, thank you
for bringing me.

1:10:38.993 --> 1:10:41.202
The priest said he
was cremated here.

1:10:41.237 --> 1:10:45.448
[birds squawking]
[Shania sighs]

1:10:45.482 --> 1:10:47.726
So this is where
it happens, huh?

1:10:48.658 --> 1:10:49.900
- Yes.

1:10:49.935 --> 1:10:52.006
This is where the town
brings their dead.

1:10:53.179 --> 1:10:53.939
Last rites.

1:10:57.943 --> 1:10:58.840
They bring the dead bodies here

1:10:58.875 --> 1:11:00.048
and then just

1:11:01.671 --> 1:11:02.741
turn them into flames.

1:11:03.776 --> 1:11:06.641
[melancholy music]

1:11:08.194 --> 1:11:10.127
- You know, I always wonder

1:11:12.613 --> 1:11:15.063
how people lose their
identities once they're dead.

1:11:16.375 --> 1:11:18.929
For everyone, you're,
you're just a body.

1:11:24.349 --> 1:11:25.211
You know, I,

1:11:27.490 --> 1:11:28.801
I was sitting right there,
throughout.

1:11:32.046 --> 1:11:33.427
I didn't leave my dad alone.

1:11:37.154 --> 1:11:38.155
Everybody else left.

1:11:40.296 --> 1:11:41.193
I was right there.

1:11:45.266 --> 1:11:47.026
I'm sure he's always with me.

1:11:49.166 --> 1:11:52.308
- Dad said we'd come back
as an animal or as a human

1:11:52.342 --> 1:11:55.345
to catch up with who we love.

1:11:55.380 --> 1:11:59.660
[chuckles] He said he'd return
as a pigeon just to see me.

1:12:04.941 --> 1:12:06.114
Look at all those birds.

1:12:07.944 --> 1:12:09.842
I wonder if one of
them is a pigeon.

1:12:13.018 --> 1:12:14.157
- It's not yours to find.

1:12:15.296 --> 1:12:16.159
It'll will find you.

1:12:21.682 --> 1:12:23.166
[sighs] Come on now.

1:12:23.200 --> 1:12:25.306
I'm sure your dad wouldn't
wanna see you like this.

1:12:26.169 --> 1:12:29.931
- Yeah, you're right.

1:12:29.966 --> 1:12:30.760
- Come.

1:12:35.937 --> 1:12:38.837
[melancholy music]

1:12:42.875 --> 1:12:46.223
[car horn beeps loudly]

1:12:51.367 --> 1:12:55.854
[chuckles] You want
me to carry you again?

1:12:55.888 --> 1:13:00.272
- I think I got this. [laughs]

1:13:00.306 --> 1:13:03.033
[car horn beeps]

1:13:09.454 --> 1:13:12.595
[upbeat Indian music]

1:13:16.426 --> 1:13:17.220
So pretty.

1:13:18.221 --> 1:13:19.049
- It's Indian.

1:13:23.191 --> 1:13:24.020
- Wow.

1:13:25.539 --> 1:13:26.402
- Indian.

1:13:31.890 --> 1:13:32.718
Indian.

1:13:33.788 --> 1:13:34.617
Very much Indian.

1:13:39.518 --> 1:13:42.452
[speaks in foreign language]

1:13:42.487 --> 1:13:45.490
- I can't believe
how much it hurts.

1:13:47.492 --> 1:13:52.497
- Yeah, I know.

1:13:57.467 --> 1:13:58.744
- Does it ever get better?

1:14:02.714 --> 1:14:04.957
- I still see his face
sometimes.

1:14:04.992 --> 1:14:06.890
I'm not sure if it
ever gets better.

1:14:08.720 --> 1:14:10.031
But I guess you accept it.

1:14:12.448 --> 1:14:13.621
Learn to live with the pain.

1:14:21.284 --> 1:14:23.182
You know anything about physics?

1:14:23.217 --> 1:14:24.218
- [Shania] Yeah, why?

1:14:25.978 --> 1:14:26.979
- Energy never dies.

1:14:28.153 --> 1:14:29.223
Merely changes forms.

1:14:30.811 --> 1:14:31.915
And soul is an energy,

1:14:33.296 --> 1:14:35.091
hence, it never dies.

1:14:38.197 --> 1:14:41.200
[rhythmic drumming]

1:14:43.824 --> 1:14:46.689
[speaks in foreign language]

1:14:46.723 --> 1:14:49.277
- [chuckles] What's their
health rating, a D minus?

1:14:49.312 --> 1:14:51.003
- Come on, stop
being so American.

1:14:52.557 --> 1:14:56.353
[speaks in foreign language]

1:15:16.512 --> 1:15:19.584
[mobile phone rings]

1:15:22.138 --> 1:15:23.173
Sorry, I have to take this.

1:15:23.208 --> 1:15:24.036
- Okay.

1:15:29.317 --> 1:15:30.318
- Yes, sir.

1:15:30.353 --> 1:15:32.010
- Listen Harb hajan.

1:15:32.044 --> 1:15:35.496
You insisted on
taking care of this.

1:15:35.531 --> 1:15:37.084
Is the mission complete?

1:15:37.118 --> 1:15:39.155
- Sir, I don't think she's
the problem

1:15:39.189 --> 1:15:40.018
you think with she is

1:15:40.052 --> 1:15:41.260
- [Avtar On Phone] Don't argue.

1:15:41.295 --> 1:15:43.953
You're there to get
her laptop, that's it!

1:15:43.987 --> 1:15:44.816
- Okay.

1:15:46.611 --> 1:15:48.129
You'll have to
promise me one thing.

1:15:48.164 --> 1:15:49.268
- [Avtar On Phone] Yeah.

1:15:49.303 --> 1:15:51.408
- If I get you all the stuff,

1:15:51.443 --> 1:15:53.479
she'll be able to go back home.

1:15:53.514 --> 1:15:55.792
- I promise I will let her go.

1:15:56.690 --> 1:16:01.695
[siren wails]
[car horn beeps]

1:16:41.320 --> 1:16:43.495
- I felt his spirit
at the gurdwara.

1:16:43.529 --> 1:16:44.841
They said he came everyday.

1:16:46.256 --> 1:16:49.432
I just wish he could have
seen me all grown up.

1:16:49.466 --> 1:16:51.641
- Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

1:16:51.676 --> 1:16:52.849
- It's okay.

1:16:52.884 --> 1:16:55.300
Anyway, how's your
manhunt goin'?

1:16:55.334 --> 1:16:58.406
- [chuckles] My manhunt's
fine, how's your man hunk?

1:16:58.441 --> 1:17:00.926
- [chuckles] He's
not a man hunk!

1:17:00.961 --> 1:17:02.652
- He is in picture 63!

1:17:02.687 --> 1:17:03.342
- What?

1:17:03.377 --> 1:17:04.481
What are you talking about?

1:17:04.516 --> 1:17:06.242
- Well, I think you guys
do make the cutest couple.

1:17:06.276 --> 1:17:07.208
- Oh, my goodness.

1:17:07.243 --> 1:17:08.693
Let me see.

1:17:08.727 --> 1:17:10.142
It's that one where you've got
that really gorgeous smile,

1:17:10.177 --> 1:17:12.351
and he's kinda slightly flexing.

1:17:12.386 --> 1:17:14.664
Oh, my God, it's just so hot.

1:17:14.699 --> 1:17:15.596
- Oh, my God, it's gone!

1:17:15.631 --> 1:17:16.977
- What?

1:17:17.011 --> 1:17:18.081
- [Shania] My laptop!

1:17:23.708 --> 1:17:26.642
[melancholy music]

1:17:27.919 --> 1:17:28.747
- Not hungry?

1:17:30.369 --> 1:17:31.750
Harbhajan?

1:17:31.785 --> 1:17:33.441
Dinner?

1:17:33.476 --> 1:17:34.926
- Yeah, delicious, Mamaji.

1:17:36.755 --> 1:17:38.757
- But you have to eat
it to know that.

1:17:40.138 --> 1:17:43.244
[mobile phone rings]

1:17:45.557 --> 1:17:47.421
[phone beeps]

1:17:47.455 --> 1:17:48.491
Maybe it's important.

1:17:51.011 --> 1:17:51.839
- I doubt it.

1:17:54.670 --> 1:17:55.774
- Come, wait one second.

1:17:57.534 --> 1:18:00.434
[melancholy music]

1:18:08.097 --> 1:18:09.546
- [Shania On Voicemail]
Hey, Harb, by any chance,

1:18:09.581 --> 1:18:10.755
have you seen my laptop?

1:18:12.549 --> 1:18:14.310
- [Avtar On Voicemail]
Harbhajan, I need that laptop.

1:18:14.344 --> 1:18:15.414
Where the hell are you?

1:18:15.449 --> 1:18:17.244
- [Shania On Voicemail]
Harb, please,

1:18:17.278 --> 1:18:18.590
please call me back right away.

1:18:18.624 --> 1:18:20.212
I think my laptop's been stolen!

1:18:22.663 --> 1:18:23.560
- [Avtar On Voicemail]
Hello, Harbhajan,

1:18:23.595 --> 1:18:24.976
get me that reporter laptop--

1:18:27.323 --> 1:18:30.257
[melancholy music]

1:18:35.434 --> 1:18:37.747
[loud thud]

1:18:46.445 --> 1:18:50.311
- [gasps] Oh, my God,
you found it, oh, my God!

1:18:51.657 --> 1:18:53.004
Thank you so much.

1:18:53.038 --> 1:18:53.867
- But listen.

1:18:55.075 --> 1:18:57.180
You can't publish this
article on the hijras.

1:18:57.215 --> 1:18:58.078
- What, why?

1:18:59.355 --> 1:19:00.183
- No.

1:19:01.806 --> 1:19:02.668
- Oh!

1:19:04.394 --> 1:19:05.671
Oh, I get it.

1:19:05.706 --> 1:19:07.259
So you're the one
who took my computer

1:19:07.294 --> 1:19:09.503
because you don't want
me to write this article.

1:19:10.815 --> 1:19:12.057
So, what, everything...

1:19:13.127 --> 1:19:13.990
You, me?

1:19:15.716 --> 1:19:16.855
It was all because
of the article,

1:19:16.890 --> 1:19:19.168
wasn't it?
- No, of course not!

1:19:19.202 --> 1:19:20.203
What you're saying...

1:19:21.239 --> 1:19:23.586
Listen, everything I said or...

1:19:23.620 --> 1:19:24.449
Or I didn't say.

1:19:25.346 --> 1:19:26.451
Everything I did, I...

1:19:27.832 --> 1:19:28.971
It was absolutely true.

1:19:29.903 --> 1:19:31.180
- You were spying on me!

1:19:31.214 --> 1:19:33.113
- I was spying on you because
you were spying on the hijras!

1:19:33.147 --> 1:19:34.355
You started this!

1:19:34.390 --> 1:19:36.116
- Oh, my God!

1:19:36.150 --> 1:19:37.911
I fell in love with
a six-year old!

1:19:38.981 --> 1:19:40.499
- What do you mean by
you fell in love with--

1:19:42.812 --> 1:19:43.917
Wait, wait, one second.

1:19:45.642 --> 1:19:46.471
Me?

1:19:49.923 --> 1:19:52.097
- [sighs] I can't believe
I actually thought

1:19:52.132 --> 1:19:53.547
you really understood me.

1:19:53.581 --> 1:19:56.343
[scoffs] Shania, I get you.

1:19:56.377 --> 1:19:57.931
I've been there.

1:19:57.965 --> 1:20:00.899
I wouldn't be surprised if
your dad wasn't even dead.

1:20:00.934 --> 1:20:02.142
- Don't say that.
- Oh!

1:20:02.176 --> 1:20:03.419
Maybe that's your
dad over there!

1:20:03.453 --> 1:20:04.454
Hey, excuse me!

1:20:04.489 --> 1:20:05.593
Are you his dad?

1:20:05.628 --> 1:20:06.698
- Shania.
- Or maybe, maybe,

1:20:06.732 --> 1:20:08.251
maybe he's your dad.
- Listen.

1:20:08.286 --> 1:20:09.183
- What about that guy there?

1:20:09.218 --> 1:20:10.564
Hey, are one of you his dad?

1:20:10.598 --> 1:20:12.117
- What are you doing?

1:20:12.152 --> 1:20:13.084
What are you doing?

1:20:15.569 --> 1:20:17.329
I won't lie about
something like that.

1:20:18.296 --> 1:20:19.538
- Why should I believe you?

1:20:19.573 --> 1:20:20.954
- Because I care about you, too.

1:20:22.438 --> 1:20:23.853
- Yeah.
- And it's the only way

1:20:23.888 --> 1:20:26.338
to convince them to not
bring up charges against you.

1:20:26.373 --> 1:20:27.926
So you need to understand!

1:20:27.961 --> 1:20:28.824
Shania!

1:20:35.140 --> 1:20:35.969
- [sighs]

1:20:37.384 --> 1:20:38.557
I will miss her.

1:20:40.766 --> 1:20:41.595
- I'm sure.

1:20:43.493 --> 1:20:47.256
- Maybe, I will see her
when I move to America.

1:20:49.258 --> 1:20:50.362
What about you, Sirji?

1:20:54.125 --> 1:20:56.610
[mobile phone rings]

1:20:56.644 --> 1:20:58.198
- Hey, Whit.
- Hey!

1:20:58.232 --> 1:20:59.889
So I just finished
reading your article.

1:20:59.924 --> 1:21:02.064
Well, that's not true,
I finished my champs

1:21:02.098 --> 1:21:04.756
but I did read your
article and I love it!

1:21:04.790 --> 1:21:07.276
Sweetie, I think you
really pulled this one off!

1:21:07.310 --> 1:21:08.760
- [Shania] No, I didn't!

1:21:08.794 --> 1:21:09.588
- [Whitney] Honey,
sweetie, what's wrong?

1:21:09.623 --> 1:21:10.486
Are you okay?

1:21:10.520 --> 1:21:12.798
- I rebooked my flight,
I'm coming home!

1:21:12.833 --> 1:21:14.110
- Why, what happened?

1:21:14.145 --> 1:21:15.767
- He screwed me over!

1:21:15.801 --> 1:21:17.493
And not the way you're thinking!

1:21:17.527 --> 1:21:19.598
I'm gonna rename this
article Four Weddings

1:21:19.633 --> 1:21:21.877
and a Screw-Over! [sobs]

1:21:21.911 --> 1:21:22.705
- Oh,

1:21:22.739 --> 1:21:23.533
my

1:21:23.568 --> 1:21:24.500
God!

1:21:24.534 --> 1:21:25.363
You're in love!

1:21:26.778 --> 1:21:29.850
[mobile phone rings]

1:21:32.991 --> 1:21:34.993
[sighs]

1:21:36.443 --> 1:21:37.893
- Yes, sir.

1:21:37.927 --> 1:21:39.756
[Avtar speaks in
foreign language]

1:21:39.791 --> 1:21:41.586
Yes, sir, I have it.

1:21:44.865 --> 1:21:46.004
Yeah, we'll be right there, sir.

1:21:46.039 --> 1:21:48.179
Actually, we're stuck
in traffic, sir.

1:21:49.076 --> 1:21:50.733
Move your car, move!

1:21:50.767 --> 1:21:52.700
- Hello, Harbhajan?
- Yes, sir?

1:21:52.735 --> 1:21:54.599
[Avtar speaks in
foreign language]

1:21:54.633 --> 1:21:56.394
Yeah, we'll be right there.

1:21:56.428 --> 1:21:58.051
- [Avtar On Phone]
I am waiting, okay?

1:22:00.363 --> 1:22:01.433
- That'll hold him off

1:22:03.263 --> 1:22:04.954
hopefully long enough for
her to get on that plane

1:22:04.989 --> 1:22:05.817
and head home.

1:22:07.992 --> 1:22:11.961
- [sighs] Sirji, you know you
could go to jail for this.

1:22:16.966 --> 1:22:18.934
You are willing to
go that far for her?

1:22:20.418 --> 1:22:22.696
[chuckles] Yet, you
won't send her back

1:22:22.730 --> 1:22:25.319
with the one thing
she really wants.

1:22:27.425 --> 1:22:29.047
- What would that be?

1:22:29.082 --> 1:22:30.428
- She told you.

1:22:30.462 --> 1:22:31.981
She loves you.

1:22:32.016 --> 1:22:35.812
And she's leaving without
you telling her you love her.

1:22:39.368 --> 1:22:40.300
- It's not a movie.

1:22:41.439 --> 1:22:45.167
- Of course not
because those are fake.

1:22:45.201 --> 1:22:47.100
But love is real.

1:22:47.134 --> 1:22:49.033
And you're really
wasting time, Sirji.

1:22:52.208 --> 1:22:53.899
You still have an
hour to fix it.

1:22:55.039 --> 1:22:57.386
And if I have your
permission to speed

1:22:57.420 --> 1:22:59.526
I can get you there
in 45 minutes.

1:23:00.561 --> 1:23:03.219
[playful music]

1:23:08.362 --> 1:23:10.916
[police siren wails]

1:23:10.951 --> 1:23:13.678
[car horn beeps]

1:23:28.072 --> 1:23:31.868
Urgency, Urgency!

1:23:39.152 --> 1:23:43.052
[speaking in foreign language]

1:23:44.502 --> 1:23:45.710
- Flight to New York, please.

1:23:45.744 --> 1:23:47.470
- Sorry, sir, our
counter has closed.

1:23:47.505 --> 1:23:49.610
- Listen, there's this
passenger named Shania Dhaliwal.

1:23:49.645 --> 1:23:51.267
I really have to talk to her.

1:23:51.302 --> 1:23:52.648
It's very urgent.
- Sorry, sir,

1:23:52.682 --> 1:23:53.959
I can't do anything, sorry.
- Please, I'm sure

1:23:53.994 --> 1:23:55.133
you can do something!

1:23:55.168 --> 1:23:56.376
It's very urgent!
- Sorry, sir!

1:23:56.410 --> 1:23:57.722
Our counter's closed.
- I have to talk to her!

1:23:57.756 --> 1:23:58.964
Please try and understand!
- Sorry, sir.

1:23:58.999 --> 1:24:00.380
I can't do anything!
- Excuse me, yes.

1:24:00.414 --> 1:24:01.622
What happened?

1:24:01.657 --> 1:24:02.865
- No, listen, there's
a flight to New York

1:24:02.899 --> 1:24:04.211
and there's a passenger
named Shania Dhaliwal.

1:24:04.246 --> 1:24:05.454
I really have to talk to her.

1:24:05.488 --> 1:24:07.111
- Which flight, this flight?
- To New York, to New York.

1:24:07.145 --> 1:24:09.251
- No, the flight has departed.

1:24:09.285 --> 1:24:10.666
- Listen, please, please
try and do something.

1:24:10.700 --> 1:24:12.495
If you would just...

1:24:12.530 --> 1:24:15.188
[mobile phone rings]

1:24:15.222 --> 1:24:16.189
Yes, sir?

1:24:16.223 --> 1:24:17.190
- [Avtar On Phone] Harbhajan?

1:24:17.224 --> 1:24:19.744
- Sir, I'm on my way
and the laptop is here

1:24:19.778 --> 1:24:20.676
right in my hand.

1:24:20.710 --> 1:24:22.505
- [Avtar On Phone] No, it's not.

1:24:22.540 --> 1:24:24.266
Because it's right
here in my hand.

1:24:27.510 --> 1:24:28.339
- Okay, sir.

1:24:29.926 --> 1:24:32.826
[soft knocking]

1:24:32.860 --> 1:24:34.069
Sir, I can totally exp--

1:24:36.657 --> 1:24:37.486
Hey.

1:24:40.213 --> 1:24:41.317
What, what happened?

1:24:42.767 --> 1:24:44.458
- Ms. Dhaliwal
decided to turn in

1:24:44.493 --> 1:24:47.047
all of her materials voluntarily

1:24:47.082 --> 1:24:49.325
in order to keep you
from getting in trouble.

1:24:51.327 --> 1:24:52.811
Why don't you take
her to the airport

1:24:52.846 --> 1:24:55.228
to catch the next
flight back to the US?

1:24:55.262 --> 1:24:57.333
- What are you gonna
do with my computer?

1:24:58.817 --> 1:25:01.682
- As discussed, we will make
an exception this one time.

1:25:02.718 --> 1:25:04.927
But you do need new permissions.

1:25:06.135 --> 1:25:06.963
Ah.

1:25:09.449 --> 1:25:11.485
This is a new application.

1:25:11.520 --> 1:25:14.488
You have to fill it out
and hopefully they approve.

1:25:15.765 --> 1:25:16.594
- Thank you, sir!

1:25:16.628 --> 1:25:19.459
- You're welcome.

1:25:19.493 --> 1:25:21.564
- I will take that.
- Yeah, sure.

1:25:23.704 --> 1:25:25.913
- One more thing, Ms. Dhaliwal.

1:25:25.948 --> 1:25:28.606
Being a journalist, you
have some responsibilities

1:25:28.640 --> 1:25:29.469
to be fair.

1:25:30.746 --> 1:25:32.748
there are some new
rules in this country

1:25:34.059 --> 1:25:37.028
and hijras are considered
as third gender.

1:25:37.062 --> 1:25:39.893
But for things to change,
laws are not enough.

1:25:40.756 --> 1:25:41.860
People have to change.

1:25:44.415 --> 1:25:45.243
Bye-bye.

1:25:46.106 --> 1:25:47.038
- Thank you.

1:25:47.072 --> 1:25:48.419
- [Avtar] Have a nice flight.

1:25:54.977 --> 1:25:57.290
[both sigh]

1:26:01.328 --> 1:26:04.331
- Hey.

1:26:04.366 --> 1:26:09.371
Are you really leaving?

1:26:11.235 --> 1:26:14.376
[upbeat Indian music]

1:26:44.095 --> 1:26:46.097
[sighs]

1:26:51.240 --> 1:26:55.382
[woman sings in
foreign language]

1:27:24.308 --> 1:27:27.380
[pigeon coos softly]

1:27:52.888 --> 1:27:56.650
["U U Yeah" by Daler Mehndi]
